    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a paragraph on the topic of </span><span class=\"english\">“Adversities of a Street Child”.</span><span class=\"english\">                              10</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Adversities of a Street Child</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">A street child faces countless adversities and hardships from the very beginning of life. Without proper shelter or family care, he lives on roads, footpaths, railway stations, or under open skies. Hunger becomes his constant companion as he searches for food from dustbins or survives by begging. He does not get the chance to go to school, so he grows up uneducated, helpless, and unaware of his rights. Society often looks down on him and treats him </span><span class=\"english\">with neglect, indifference, or even cruelty. To survive, many street children are forced into hazardous child labor or petty crimes. They live in dirty surroundings, which expose them to dangerous diseases without medical care. During stormy nights, cold winters, or heavy rains, they suffer terribly with no protection. Their innocent childhood is stolen away by misery, struggle, and endless pain. It is the duty of both government and society to save them, educate them, and ensure a brighter future.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Highest Marks----------------------------------------------------------------09 Marks</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">(A) For Title (</span><span class=\"english\">Adversities of a Street Child</span><span class=\"english\">)------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Mark</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Topic Sentence (Introduction)</span><span class=\"english\"> -------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">A street child faces countless adversities and hardships from the very beginning of life. </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(C) </span><span class=\"english\">Street Children's Struggles and Rights </span><span class=\"english\">( Any</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">06)</span><span class=\"english\">------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">06 Marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">• Street children live without shelter or family care, surviving on roads, footpaths,</span><span class=\"english\"> railway stations</span><span class=\"english\"> or under open skies.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Hunger and lack of education lead to uneducated, helpless, and unaware youth.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Society often treats them with neglect, indifference, or cruelty.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Many street children are forced into hazardous child labor or petty crimes.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Living in dirty surroundings exposes them to dangerous diseases without medical care.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Stormy nights, cold winters, and heavy rains cause severe suffering.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Their innocent childhood is ruined by misery, struggle, and pain.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(D) Conclusion</span><span class=\"english\">-----------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">It is the duty of both government and society to save them, educate them, and ensure a brighter future.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. </span><span class=\"english\">For every 3 spelling/grammatical mistakes, 01 mark has to be deducted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2. </span><span class=\"english\">Students must write within a para. If a student writes more than one para, half of the deserving marks must be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Comment: Write within single/one para)</span><span class=\"english\">.</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3.</span><span class=\"english\"> For writing only the title of the paragraph bears no mark.</span><span> </span><span> </span></p>"
    },
