        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Separated = The two best friends were sadly </span><span class=\"english\">separated</span><span class=\"english\"> by distance but stayed connected through calls.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Nausea= She felt a wave of </span><span class=\"english\">nausea</span><span class=\"english\"> after eating food from a roadside stall.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Vertical= The rocket made a </span><span class=\"english\">vertical</span><span class=\"english\"> landing on the moon.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Peel off= He used a towel to </span><span class=\"english\">peel off</span><span class=\"english\"> the old sticker from the table.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Dump= The company was fined for using the riverbank as a </span><span class=\"english\">dump</span><span class=\"english\"> for industrial waste.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions: </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">i</span><span class=\"english\">) Any correct and logically meaningful sentence will be accepted. (</span><span class=\"english\">Sentences with weak meaning will not be allowed.)</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(ii) For any grammatical or structural mistake, full marks have to be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">Examiners have to show and correct the mistake(s) in the scripts.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(iii) For 02 spelling mistakes, 01 mark will be deducted, for 01 spelling mistake, 0.5 marks will be deducted from that very </span><span class=\"english\">sentence.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎(iv) For changing the part of speech of the given word by adding a suffix or prefix, the full marks have to be deducted from the very number. But students can use any form if the given word is a verb (depending on the subject-verb agreement, tense, person, number, etc.).</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎</span><span class=\"english\">Comment: Use the given word without changing its parts of speech.</span></p>"
